Here's a complete example:

**XAML**
```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ItemsPage">

    <RefreshView IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}"
                 Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}">

        <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                        SelectionMode="Single"
                        SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem}"
                        EmptyView="No items found.">
            <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
                <DataTemplate>
                    <Grid Padding="12" ColumnDefinitions="*,Auto">
                        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="16" />
                        <Label Grid.Column="1" Text="{Binding Status}"
                               TextColor="Gray" />
                    </Grid>
                </DataTemplate>
            </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        </CollectionView>

    </RefreshView>
</ContentPage>
```

**ViewModel**
```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private ObservableCollection<Item> _items = new();

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isRefreshing;

    private Item? _selectedItem;
    public Item? SelectedItem
    {
        get => _selectedItem;
        set
        {
            if (SetProperty(ref _selectedItem, value) && value is not null)
            {
                // Navigate, then clear selection so the same row can be tapped again
                _nav.GoToAsync("DetailPage", new() { ["Item"] = value });
                SelectedItem = null;
            }
        }
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        try
        {
            var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
            Items = new ObservableCollection<Item>(data);
        }
        finally
        {
            IsRefreshing = false;   // stops the spinner
        }
    }
}
```

**Key binding relationships:**

| XAML Property | ViewModel Property | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `ItemsSource` | `Items` | Drives the list |
| `SelectionMode="Single"` | — | Limits to one selection |
| `SelectedItem` | `SelectedItem` (two-way) | Fires navigation on set |
| `RefreshView.Command` | `RefreshCommand` | Auto-generated by `[RelayCommand]` |
| `RefreshView.IsRefreshing` | `IsRefreshing` | Set `false` when done to hide spinner |

**Important details:**

1. **Reset `SelectedItem` to `null`** after navigating — otherwise the same row can't be tapped twice in a row.
2. **Set `IsRefreshing = false`** in a `finally` block so the spinner always stops, even on error.
3. `[RelayCommand]` from the MVVM Community Toolkit generates `RefreshCommand` from `RefreshAsync` automatically.
4. Wrap `CollectionView` inside `RefreshView` — `CollectionView` doesn't have a built-in pull-to-refresh.
